CatDescriptText: Cutline of images published in the Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 2, 1955, pg. 12 reads: "Teen-Queen Contestants - These fourteen young misses of the Hill District are vying for the title Teen-Queen in the annual contest sponsored by Hill City.  They are, left to right:...Priscilla Ward and Janet A. Gantt"
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of Priscilla Ward wearing flecked jumper over sweater and rhinestone necklace with bow, posed in front of light colored background for Hill City Teen Queen contest; Portrait of Janet A. Gantt wearing light colored blouse with rounded floral applique collar, posed in front of light colored background for Hill City Teen Queen contest
